together for domestic or professional tasks. Cyber security breaches in such
robots undermine the trust between humans and robots. In this paper, we
investigate how to apprehend and inflict security threats at the design and
implementation stage of a movable autonomous service robot. To this end, we
leverage the idea of directed fuzzing and design RoboFuzz that systematically
tests an autonomous service robot in line with the robot's states and the
surrounding environment. The methodology of RoboFuzz is to study critical
